1. Introduction

This project focuses on analyzing retail sales data to generate meaningful business insights. The goal is to build an end-to-end data analytics solution using Python, SQL, and Power BI to understand sales trends, product performance, and customer purchasing behavior.

2. Business Problem

Retail businesses often face challenges due to fragmented data across multiple sales channels. This makes it difficult to track overall performance, manage inventory efficiently, and identify top-performing products and regions.

3. Objectives
🔥Analyze sales data to identify trends
🔥Calculate key metrics like Total Revenue and Average Revenue per Order
🔥Identify best-selling products and categories
🔥Analyze sales performance across cities
🔥Identify peak purchasing hours and seasonal trends
🔥Build an interactive dashboard for decision-making
4. Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)
🔥Total RevenueTotal Revenue
🔥Total Orders
🔥Average Revenue per Order
🔥Total Quantity Sold
5. Tools & Technologies
🔥Python (Pandas, NumPy)
🔥SQL (MySQL / PostgreSQL)
🔥Power BI
🔥Microsoft Excel
🔥GitHub
6. Methodology
Week 1: Data Cleaning and Preparation
🔥Imported raw dataset into Python
🔥Handled missing values using median and default values
🔥Removed duplicate records
🔥Converted date column into datetime format
🔥Created revenue column (quantity × price)
🔥Extracted year, month, day, and hour
Week 2: SQL Database and Analysis
🔥Imported cleaned dataset into SQL database
🔥Created structured table
🔥Used SQL queries (SUM, AVG, GROUP BY, ORDER BY)
Calculated:
      🔥Total Revenue
      🔥Total Orders
      🔥Average Revenue per Order
      🔥Best-Selling Products
      🔥Sales by City
Week 3: Dashboard Development
🔥Connected dataset to Power BI
Created visualizations:
      🔥Monthly sales trend (line chart)
      🔥Product performance (bar chart)
      🔥Peak sales hours (column chart)
      🔥City-wise sales (map/bar chart)
🔥Added filters for Month, City, Category
7. Dashboard Description

The dashboard provides a complete view of retail sales performance, including trends, product analysis, geographic insights, and peak sales timings. Users can interact with the dashboard using filters to explore data dynamically.

8. Key Insights
🔥Sales show clear monthly trends indicating seasonal demand patterns
🔥A small number of products contribute to the majority of total revenue
🔥Certain cities generate significantly higher sales, indicating regional demand differences
🔥Peak purchasing activity occurs during specific hours of the day
🔥Weekday analysis shows variation in customer purchasing behavior
9. Business Recommendations
🔥Increase inventory for high-demand and high-revenue products
🔥Focus marketing campaigns on top-performing cities
🔥Run targeted promotions during peak sales periods and seasonal spikes
🔥Optimize staffing and operations during high-traffic hours
🔥Reduce stock or redesign strategy for low-performing products
10. Project Outcome
🔥Developed a complete end-to-end data analytics solution
🔥Transformed raw data into actionable business insights
🔥Built an interactive dashboard for decision-making
🔥Enabled better understanding of sales trends and customer behavior
11. Conclusion

This project demonstrates how data analytics can transform raw retail data into actionable insights. By integrating data cleaning, SQL analysis, and interactive dashboards, the solution helps businesses make data-driven decisions and improve sales and inventory management.

